definition.value: The lipid bilayer surrounding any of the thin, flattened compartments that form the central portion of the Golgi complex.
The portion of the plasma membrane surrounding a growth cone.
The lipid bilayer surrounding a multivesicular body.
The lipid bilayer surrounding a protein storage vacuole.
The portion of the plasma membrane surrounding a ruffle.
The lipid bilayer surrounding any of the compartments that make up the trans-Golgi network.
The portion of the plasma membrane surrounding a neuron projection.
The portion of the plasma membrane surrounding a dendrite.
The portion of the plasma membrane surrounding a dendritic spine.

The component of the mitochondrial membrane consisting of the gene products that have some part that penetrates at least one leaflet of the membrane bilayer. This component includes gene products that are buried in the bilayer with no exposure outside the bilayer.
A small membrane-bounded vesicle that releases its contents by exocytosis in response to insulin stimulation -  the contents are enriched in GLUT4, IRAP and VAMP2.

A heterotrimeric protein complex formed by the association of NHE3, E3KARP and alpha-actinin upon an increase in calcium ion concentration -  found in clusters localized on plasma membrane and in intracellular compartments.
Interacting selectively and non-covalently with any protein or protein complex (a complex of two or more proteins that may include other nonprotein molecules), in the presence of copper.

A heterotrimeric H4|H2A histone acetyltransferase complex with a substrate preference of chromatin over free histones. It contains a subset of the proteins found in the larger NuA4 histone acetyltransferase complex -  for example, the S. cerevisiae complex contains Esa1p, Yng2p, and Epl1p.
Catalysis of the transfer of a solute or solutes from one side of a membrane to the other according to the reaction -  ATP + H2O + cobalt(out) -eq- ADP + phosphate + cobalt(in).
A heterodimeric protein complex that acts as an RNA polymerase II elongation factor -  the complex is conserved from yeast to humans, and is present in S. pombe, but absent from S. cerevisiae.
Interacting selectively and non-covalently with lead (Pb) ions.
Interacting selectively and non-covalently with a GTPase activating protein.
Interacting selectively and non-covalently with a heterotrimeric G-protein.

A protein complex that contains the survival motor neuron (SMN) protein and at least eight additional integral components, including the Gemin2-8 and Unrip proteins -  the complex is found in the cytoplasm and in nuclear Gems, and is involved in spliceosomal snRNP assembly in the cytoplasm and in pre-mRNA splicing in the nucleus.
A conserved DNA recombinase mediator complex that contains two Swi5 monomers and one Sfr1 monomer in Schizosaccharomyces, or orthologs thereof (e.g. Sae3p and Mei5p in Saccharomyces).
A protein complex that phosphorylates amino acid residues of RNA polymerase II C-terminal domain repeats -  phosphorylation occurs mainly on Ser2 and Ser5.

A eukaryotically conserved protein complex that contains DNA ligase IV and is involved in DNA repair by non-homologous end joining -  in addition to the ligase, the complex also contains XRCC4 or a homolog, e.g. Saccharomyces Lif1p.
The plasma membrane of a neuron cell body - excludes the plasma membrane of cell projections such as axons and dendrites.
Interacting selectively and non-covalently with the sterol response element (SRE), a nonpalindromic sequence found in the promoters of genes involved in lipid metabolism.

label.value: tumor necrosis factor receptor superfamily binding

definition.value: Interacting selectively and non-covalently with any member of the tumor necrosis factor receptor superfamily.

label.value: regulation of natural killer cell proliferation

definition.value: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of natural killer cell proliferation.

label.value: negative regulation of natural killer cell proliferation

definition.value: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of natural killer cell proliferation.

label.value: positive regulation of natural killer cell proliferation

definition.value: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of natural killer cell proliferation.

label.value: regulation of natural killer cell proliferation involved in immune response

definition.value: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of natural killer cell proliferation as part of an immune response.

label.value: negative regulation of natural killer cell proliferation involved in immune response

definition.value: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of natural killer cell proliferation as part of an immune response.

label.value: positive regulation of natural killer cell proliferation involved in immune response

definition.value: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of natural killer cell proliferation as part of an immune response.

The cell cycle process in which genetic material, in the form of chromosomes, is organized and then physically separated and apportioned to two or more sets during a normally chiasmate meiosis under the condition that chiasma have not occurred between a particular pair of homologs. Distributive segregation is a \'backup\' mechanism to ensure the segregation of homologs that have failed to cross over - either as a consequence of mutation or not, as, for example, the 4th chromosome of Drosophila melanogaster (which never exchanges, presumably due to its small size) - but nevertheless segregate normally.
All of the contents of a cell projection, excluding the plasma membrane surrounding the projection.
All of the contents of a dendrite, excluding the surrounding plasma membrane.
Interacting selectively and non-covalently with a proline-rich region within the same polypeptide.

Interacting selectively and non-covalently with calcitonin, a peptide hormone responsible for reducing serum calcium levels by inhibiting osteoclastic bone reabsorption and promoting renal calcium excretion. It is synthesized and released by the C cells of the thyroid.
Catalysis of the reaction -  2 RSH + ROOH -eq- RSSR + ROH + H2O. This reaction is the thiol-dependent conversion of an organic hydroperoxide to the corresponding alcohol.

A protein complex that links the endoplasmic reticulum with mitochondria and may have a role in promoting exchange of calcium and phospholipids between the two organelles. The complex is also associated with actively replicating mitochondrial DNA nucleoids, and may further coordinate mitochondrial genome replication and membrane growth.
Catalysis of the reaction -  D-xylitol + NADP+ -eq- D-xylose + NADPH + H+.
Catalysis of the reaction -  L-arabitol + NADP+ -eq- L-arabinose + NADPH + H+.
Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of DNA endoreduplication.
Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of DNA endoreduplication.
Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of DNA endoreduplication.
Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of the cell cycle process in which the distance is lengthened between poles of the spindle.
Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of the cell cycle process in which the distance is lengthened between poles of the mitotic spindle.
Catalysis of the reaction -  palmitoyl-CoA + AH2 + O2 -eq- palmitoleic acid (16 - 1delta9) + A + 2 H2O.
A complex consisting of 4 protein subunits as a heterotetramer, that possesses sarcosine oxidase activity.
Catalysis of the reaction -  acetyl-CoA + histone H3 L-lysine (position 56) -eq- CoA + histone H3 N6-acetyl-L-lysine (position 56).

label.value: negative regulation of astral microtubule depolymerization

definition.value: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of the depolymerization of astral microtubules.
